to younger people,

00:24:47.720 --> 00:24:50.150
sometimes my
experience is that when

00:24:50.150 --> 00:24:51.650
you talk to people
about meditation,

00:24:51.650 --> 00:24:53.275
or you're having a
discussion about it,

00:24:53.275 --> 00:24:57.270
they tend to have this
almost cartoonish image of,

00:24:57.270 --> 00:24:59.767
you're a swami on
the Ganges in India,

00:24:59.767 --> 00:25:01.100
you know, and you're meditating.

00:25:01.100 --> 00:25:02.000
RUSSELL SIMMONS: I'm a Swami?

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:04.000
AUDIENCE: No, the person
that you're talking to.

00:25:04.000 --> 00:25:05.810
Maybe you are, I don't know.

00:25:05.810 --> 00:25:09.010
But I'm just
wondering, particularly

00:25:09.010 --> 00:25:12.160
in terms of sort of rolling
it out to young people-- who

00:25:12.160 --> 00:25:14.600
tend to be more
skeptical, I would

00:25:14.600 --> 00:25:17.570
think, of these kinds of
things-- how you plan,

00:25:17.570 --> 00:25:20.450
or if you've had
successes overcoming

00:25:20.450 --> 00:25:22.575
this sort of knee
jerk reaction to it?

00:25:22.575 --> 00:25:24.700
RUSSELL SIMMONS: Well, I've
had lots of experiences

00:25:24.700 --> 00:25:27.635
where I got people who would
not have meditated to meditate.

00:25:30.520 --> 00:25:32.890
Ellen DeGeneres, I'm on her
show, I talked her into it,

00:25:32.890 --> 00:25:37.420
she got the meditation
teacher, she joined the board.

00:25:37.420 --> 00:25:40.660
Oprah Winfrey, I was on her
show, we talked about it,

00:25:40.660 --> 00:25:43.530
she took in a meditation
teacher, she taught her staff,

00:25:43.530 --> 00:25:45.020
she's not only
joined the board--

00:25:45.020 --> 00:25:48.140
she's the queen of
America's new consciousness.

00:25:48.140 --> 00:25:50.430
This idea, not
necessarily religious,

00:25:50.430 --> 00:25:52.940
but the spiritual
awakening that's

00:25:52.940 --> 00:25:54.630
happening in some
parts of America,

00:25:54.630 --> 00:25:58.480
with some people in America,
Oprah is the queen of it.

00:25:58.480 --> 00:26:01.030
And opened up lots of
people's minds about it.

00:26:01.030 --> 00:26:03.690
In the schools that we have in
both, respectively, in Africa,

00:26:03.690 --> 00:26:06.500
and these people
sit in Quiet Time.

00:26:06.500 --> 00:26:08.820
So they help to spread the word.

00:26:08.820 --> 00:26:14.800
And lots of people, I mean even
Puffy-- P Diddy, a meditator?

00:26:14.800 --> 00:26:16.800
So I taught him to meditate.

00:26:16.800 --> 00:26:20.210
So yeah, people
would not meditate,

00:26:20.210 --> 00:26:22.189
a lot more of them
are meditating.

00:26:22.189 --> 00:26:24.730
AUDIENCE: But what about young
people, that was the question.

00:26:24.730 --> 00:26:25.770
Have you found them
more receptive?

00:26:25.770 --> 00:26:28.353
RUSSELL SIMMONS: I like to think
of P Diddy as a young person,

00:26:28.353 --> 00:26:30.480
because that makes
me think I'm young.

00:26:30.480 --> 00:26:32.430
No, I mean this-- no.

00:26:32.430 --> 00:26:36.320
I go to schools sometimes, and
work with principals and people

00:26:36.320 --> 00:26:38.550
like-- I've been in
schools like, lots of them,

00:26:38.550 --> 00:26:43.030
but I'm thinking in particular
about Dr. Rutherford's school

00:26:43.030 --> 00:26:47.070
in Washington, DC, in the hood,
where they were so violent.

00:26:47.070 --> 00:26:49.840
And he's just turned the school
around-- the middle school

00:26:49.840 --> 00:26:53.100
and the high school
around dramatically--

00:26:53.100 --> 00:26:54.910
through Quiet Time.

00:26:54.910 --> 00:26:57.680
He's a Maharishi, a real
transcendental meditation guy,

00:26:57.680 --> 00:27:00.237
he taught them all, they
all have their own mantra.

00:27:00.237 --> 00:27:01.695
He did the work,
and the school has

00:27:01.695 --> 00:27:05.260
a dramatic shift in everything.

00:27:05.260 --> 00:27:09.940
Graduation rates, the scholastic
improvement is dramatic,

00:27:09.940 --> 00:27:13.610
the reduction in violence
is dramatic, everything.

00:27:13.610 --> 00:27:16.960
Complete turnaround.

00:27:16.960 --> 00:27:19.170
I think I relate to
kids a little better

00:27:19.170 --> 00:27:22.360
than some of the people.

00:27:22.360 --> 00:27:24.510
I'm not ideal, it's
not like I'm Drake .

00:27:24.510 --> 00:27:26.046
You know what I mean?

00:27:26.046 --> 00:27:27.140
But I can talk to Drake.

00:27:27.140 --> 00:27:30.490
Drake would pick the phone up
if I call him, which is good.

00:27:34.190 --> 00:27:35.635
Justin Bieber sent
me a tweet that

00:27:35.635 --> 00:27:38.040
said, Uncle Rush,
teach me to meditate.

00:27:38.040 --> 00:27:39.330
Sent me a tweet.

00:27:39.330 --> 00:27:41.640
I was like, retweet
that shit, retweet that.

00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:43.740
We'll sell some books.

00:27:43.740 --> 00:27:45.180
Rita Ora, the it girl.

00:27:45.180 --> 00:27:49.260
My daughter is in love with
this new singer, Rita Ora.

00:27:49.260 --> 00:27:51.010
You guys all know
who she is, right?

00:27:51.010 --> 00:27:52.400
In love with her.

00:27:52.400 --> 00:27:56.160
She tweeted out that she's
really enjoying my book.

00:27:56.160 --> 00:27:58.610
It's big deal, because
my daughter's 14,

00:27:58.610 --> 00:28:00.500
and Rita Ora just
told her that she's

00:28:00.500 --> 00:28:02.500
enjoying my book on meditation.

00:28:02.500 --> 00:28:06.310
And then Khloe
Kardashian tweeted out,

00:28:06.310 --> 00:28:08.730
my Sunday afternoon--
I asked her to,

00:28:08.730 --> 00:28:11.300
but then she read it, and
called me, and said I loved it.

00:28:11.300 --> 00:28:14.602
Because she has eight
million Instagram followers--

00:28:14.602 --> 00:28:17.060
and I don't know how many, she
must have 20 million Twitter

00:28:17.060 --> 00:28:20.810
followers-- and she
Instagramed and tweeted it out.

00:28:20.810 --> 00:28:25.130
That's how I made the best
seller list, Khloe Kardashian.

00:28:25.130 --> 00:28:31.540
So that kind of support system,
changing young people's minds

00:28:31.540 --> 00:28:34.000
about it, that's the process.

00:28:34.000 --> 00:28:35.870
And they need it.

00:28:35.870 --> 00:28:37.530
They're the ones
with the anxiety,

00:28:37.530 --> 00:28:40.970
they're the ones who are worried
that they're not good enough.

00:28:40.970 --> 00:28:42.890
Never mind that half
of you are like,

00:28:42.890 --> 00:28:47.170
oh my god, you wake up
nervous, anxiety, over nothing.

00:28:47.170 --> 00:28:49.870
And meditation teaches
us it's nothing, really.

00:28:49.870 --> 00:28:51.090
Right?

00:28:51.090 --> 00:28:51.590
[INAUDIBLE]

00:28:54.670 --> 00:28:58.950
AUDIENCE: You mentioned
earlier that major thinkers

00:28:58.950 --> 00:29:04.830
and philosophers throughout
time have said over and over,

00:29:04.830 --> 00:29:07.130
in various different
ways, that stillness

00:29:07.130 --> 00:29:09.560
is the link to happiness.

00:29:09.560 --> 00:29:12.214
And that every religion
has said in its own way.

00:29:12.214 --> 00:29:13.880
And I was wondering,
in your experience,

00:29:13.880 --> 00:29:15.570
if you had any
religious background

00:29:15.570 --> 00:29:19.760
that either contributed to
your involvement in meditation,

00:29:19.760 --> 00:29:21.910
or how it might
have played into it?

00:29:21.910 --> 00:29:23.335
RUSSELL SIMMONS:
Well, I told you,

00:29:23.335 --> 00:29:25.890
I think, it was because
of chicks in class.

00:29:25.890 --> 00:29:27.330
That was 20 years ago.

00:29:27.330 --> 00:29:30.126
I like to say it because
it's stupid, people laugh.

00:29:30.126 --> 00:29:33.560
It's not that
stupid, [INAUDIBLE].

00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:36.360
My brother's a
preacher, he's a kind

00:29:36.360 --> 00:29:40.870
of non-conventional preacher.

00:29:40.870 --> 00:29:44.110
My father and mother
are Christians.

00:29:44.110 --> 00:29:46.320
I fainted, I was like
12, or something--

00:29:46.320 --> 00:29:47.945
I don't know why, I
never fainted again

00:29:47.945 --> 00:29:50.112
for the rest of my life--
I fainted at the bus stop,

00:29:50.112 --> 00:29:51.111
coming home from church.

00:29:51.111 --> 00:29:52.280
They never made me go again.

00:29:52.280 --> 00:29:54.029
Like I don't know, I
could have staged it,

00:29:54.029 --> 00:29:55.600
but I didn't, it just happened.

00:29:55.600 --> 00:29:57.760
And they came and got me,
and said, what happened?

00:29:57.760 --> 00:29:58.130
You fell down.

00:29:58.130 --> 00:29:59.260
You were out for two seconds.

00:29:59.260 --> 00:29:59.910
We took you to the doctor.

00:29:59.910 --> 00:30:00.544
All right, OK.

00:30:00.544 --> 00:30:02.460
Mom picked me up from
the doctor, that was it,

00:30:02.460 --> 00:30:04.290
I never had to go
to church again.

00:30:04.290 --> 00:30:07.060
Now I go to churches to
speak about meditation,

00:30:07.060 --> 00:30:10.000
or about spiritual matters.

00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:13.740
But I do read all the
propaganda associated with yoga.

00:30:13.740 --> 00:30:16.700
The Yoga Sutras, the Bhagavad
Gita, the Hatha Yoga Pradipika,

00:30:16.700 --> 00:30:18.930
the Textbook of Yoga
Psychology, you know,

00:30:18.930 --> 00:30:21.280
all the Yogananda stuff,
I've read all that stuff.

00:30:21.280 --> 00:30:25.050
I like that, because
it's non-religious--

00:30:25.050 --> 00:30:27.390
until you get to some
of the deity stuff,

00:30:27.390 --> 00:30:30.200
and that relates to Hindu
stuff-- but before that,

00:30:30.200 --> 00:30:34.070
the Yoga Sutras is only a
science book for happiness.

00:30:34.070 --> 00:30:38.915
The core-- 6,000 years ago this
Yoga Sutras-- and you read it,

00:30:38.915 --> 00:30:40.040
and it's like, so relevant.

00:30:40.040 --> 00:30:44.580
It's like 194 threads-- a
sutra is a thread-- So the Yoga

00:30:44.580 --> 00:30:45.550
Sutras.

00:30:45.550 --> 00:30:48.910
And yoga is-- the
second sutra is

00:30:48.910 --> 00:30:51.410
[SPEAKING SANSKRIT] in Sanskrit.

00:30:51.410 --> 00:30:55.690
It means, yoga is a cessation
of the fluctuation of the mind.

00:30:55.690 --> 00:30:59.675
Or God Consciousness comes
when the mind is still.

00:30:59.675 --> 00:31:01.360
And that's beautiful, that's it.

00:31:04.830 --> 00:31:07.310
We all know we-- you know
you came out of the ocean,

00:31:07.310 --> 00:31:09.640
and you grew a lung,
and you stood up--

00:31:09.640 --> 00:31:11.100
you know that, right?

00:31:11.100 --> 00:31:13.450
That Adam and Eve shit is
hard to digest [INAUDIBLE].

00:31:13.450 --> 00:31:18.110
So you know that you came out
of the ocean, you grew a lung,

00:31:18.110 --> 00:31:20.950
we believe that, some of us.

00:31:20.950 --> 00:31:23.620
And I like what
Krishna said, and what

00:31:23.620 --> 00:31:27.380
yogis have said about union.

00:31:27.380 --> 00:31:29.380
If God were the ocean,
we would be a cup of God.

00:31:29.380 --> 00:31:31.160
Why do I believe that now?

00:31:31.160 --> 00:31:34.651
Because quantum physicists are
starting to believe it too.

00:31:34.651 --> 00:31:35.150
Right?

00:31:35.150 --> 00:31:37.180
That we're all connected--
all the animals

00:31:37.180 --> 00:31:39.350
we abuse, all the
planet we fuck up,

00:31:39.350 --> 00:31:42.150
all this shit we're with--
that's us we're fucking with,

00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:43.170
us.

00:31:43.170 --> 00:31:44.020
We're all connected.

00:31:44.020 --> 00:31:48.930
So that's a spiritual-- but
in the basis of a lot of what

00:31:48.930 --> 00:31:51.920
the prophets said too, although
it's not what we teach,

00:31:51.920 --> 00:31:53.960
it's separation to me.

00:31:53.960 --> 00:31:57.330
I'm not knocking religion, but
it's kind of separate in cases,

00:31:57.330 --> 00:31:59.901
and you have to double
check what they tell you.

00:31:59.901 --> 00:32:00.400
All right?

00:32:00.400 --> 00:32:03.004
The imams, rabbis, preachers,
they might say some shit,

00:32:03.004 --> 00:32:04.420
might put some
people [INAUDIBLE],

00:32:04.420 --> 00:32:06.350
they might do anything.

00:32:06.350 --> 00:32:09.160
They do horrible stuff,
religious leaders.

00:32:09.160 --> 00:32:10.860
So I kind of shy
away from all that,

00:32:10.860 --> 00:32:14.970
even though I'm the chairman
of the Foundation for Ethnic

00:32:14.970 --> 00:32:17.660
Understanding, and I
have imams and rabbis

00:32:17.660 --> 00:32:22.692
in 40 countries exchanging
pulpits and working together.

00:32:22.692 --> 00:32:24.400
Including, in Israel
we have 20 programs,

00:32:24.400 --> 00:32:26.960
so it's a real--
I really believe

00:32:26.960 --> 00:32:28.900
in religion as a way
of helping people,

00:32:28.900 --> 00:32:31.166
but I don't personally
subscribe to any.

00:32:31.166 --> 00:32:32.130
CHRIS MORROW: Well
how about this though,

00:32:32.130 --> 00:32:33.838
I had an incident--
and this kind of ties

00:32:33.838 --> 00:32:36.920
into your question-- on
Easter Sunday, where my aunt--

00:32:36.920 --> 00:32:40.420
who's a born again Christian,
and very serious about that--

00:32:40.420 --> 00:32:43.270
came up to me, and took
me aside, and said,

00:32:43.270 --> 00:32:45.670
she'd read the book-- and I
could tell she was a little

00:32:45.670 --> 00:32:51.040
nervous-- and she was concerned
that meditation would interfere

00:32:51.040 --> 00:32:52.270
with, or kind of--

00:32:52.270 --> 00:32:54.436
RUSSELL SIMMONS: Thinking
for yourself is a problem.

00:32:54.436 --> 00:32:56.750
CHRIS MORROW: Well, hey.

